2.3 Measures of central tendency

2.3.1 Mean
例2-2 计算例2-1某医院138名正常成年女性的红细胞数的均数。

max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  mean()
#&gt; [1] 127.6555



2.3.2 Median
计算例2-1某医院138名正常成年女性的红细胞数的中位数和四分位数：

max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  median()
#&gt; [1] 126

2.4 Measures of dispersion
以例2-1某医院138名正常成年女性的红细胞数为例，计算描述离散趋势的统计指标：

2.4.1 Range

range(max_hr) |&gt; 
  diff()
#&gt; [1] 135



2.4.2 Quartile and percentile

max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  quantile(probs = c(0.25, 0.5, 0.75)) 
#&gt;    25%    50%    75% 
#&gt; 112.00 126.00 144.25

In R, you can calculate the interquartile range (IQR) of a numeric variable using the IQR() function. Here’s how you can do it:

max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  IQR()
#&gt; [1] 32.25



2.4.3 Variance

max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  var()
#&gt; [1] 546.9482



2.4.4 Standard deviation

max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  sd()
#&gt; [1] 23.38692



2.4.5 变异系数

mean &lt;- max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  mean()

sd &lt;- max_hr |&gt; 
  pull() |&gt; 
  sd()

(sd / mean * 100) |&gt; 
  round(digits = 1)
#&gt; [1] 18.3
